        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued April 3 at 4:46PM MDT by NWS Denver CO</headline>
        <description>At 446 PM MDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm near
Elizabeth, or 35 miles southeast of Denver, moving northeast at 20
mph.

HAZARD...Half inch size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Minor damage to outdoor objects is possible.

Locations impacted include...
Elizabeth, Kiowa and Ponderosa Park.
</description>
        <instruction>Monitor the weather situation closely and be alert for threatening
weather conditions.</instruction>
